<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<title>O'Auth 2.0 visualisation project</title>
		<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="./css/style.css" />
		<script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.5.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
		<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="./css/jquery.steps.css" />
		<script src="js/jquery.steps.min.js"></script>
	</head>
	<body>
		<nav>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/">Homepage</a></li>
				<li><a href="/auth/login">Login</a></li>
			</ul>
		</nav>
		<main>
			<div id="stepper">
				<h3>Signing in with Gooogle</h3>
				<section>
					<p>
						It's highly likely, that you met button like this a
						thousand of times. Really comfortable way of signing in
						for user - just 2-3 clicks. But let's take a look what
						is happening under hood.
					</p>
					<p>
						<a href="/auth/google" class="google-btn unactive">
							<img src="/static/google_btn.png" />
						</a>
					</p>
				</section>
				<h3>Where it goes to</h3>
				<section>
					<p>
						1.Move your mouse over the button.<br /><br />
						2.Check in the bottom left corner address - where it
						leads to? <br /><br />
						3. /auth/google Not really looking like google servers,
						but app server will redirect to the right address.
					</p>
					<p>
						<a href="/auth/google" class="google-btn">
							<img src="/static/google_btn.png" />
						</a>
					</p>
				</section>
				<h3>Time to action</h3>
				<section>
					<p>
						You didn't click the button yet - that's good. I have to
						warn you that after clicking, we'll lose contact untill
						you sign in to your google account. Go on and we'll meet
						on the other side.
					</p>
					<p>
						<a href="/auth/google" class="google-btn">
							<img src="/static/google_btn.png" />
						</a>
					</p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</main>
	</body>
	<script>
		$('#stepper').steps({
			headerTag: 'h3',
			bodyTag: 'section',
			transitionEffect: 'slideLeft',
			autoFocus: true,
			stepsOrientation: 1,
		});
	</script>
</html>
